race.comment: PARTY FOR TWO (3) has looked impressive stringing back-to-back wins together and it's hard to knock mares in form. Gets the reliable Gollan/Lang combination and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. MANHOOD (2) grows a leg for rider Guthmann-Chester who has four wins and three placings from just seven steers. Trust that the Archibald camp has him ready to go for this first-up and should make his presence felt while fresh. HOLY RACKET (8) is another resuming but has a very handy first-up record and gets in on the minimum weight. Should give backers a sight. MAXIMUM OUTPUT (4) has won three of his past four and gets 3kg weight relief with the claim. Top-three candidate. FLAG HALL (5) next in line from the astute barn.
